@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<br />
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-3">
        <img src="~/images/logo.png" alt="The Wirral Wheelers logo" class="d-block w-100" />
        <div class="text-center font-weight-bold" style="font-size: 12px">
            Wirral Wheelers Cycling Club<br />
            Cycling UK Affiliation No: 90095292
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
            <a target="_window" href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/720974911368611/" class="right fa fa-facebook-official fa-2x white-text"></a>
            <a target="_window" href="https://www.google.com/" class="right fa fa-google-plus-official fa-2x white-text"></a>
            <a target="_window" href="https://www.instagram.com/" class="right fa fa-instagram fa-2x white-text"></a>
            <a target="_window" href="https://www.twitter.com/" class="right fa fa-twitter fa-2x white-text"></a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
        <p>Welcome to the Wirral Wheelers we are an affiliated club part of the national network of the Cycling UK</p>
        <p>We run rides starting mainly on the Wirral Peninsular &amp; Chester. There are rides every Sunday, Impromptu
            Wednesday rides, and monthly Saturday rides. We organise full day cycle rides take a look at our rides
            to see where we are going and see if any appeal to you. With rides into the lanes of Wirral, Cheshire,
            and the hillier parts of North Wales</p>
        <p>We want as many people as possible to enjoy cycling. We are a friendly group - why not come along</p>
        <p>We cycle mostly on surfaced roads at an average speed of 10-12 miles per hour - but speeds and surfaces do
            alter all you need is a normal road bike to ride with us. We arrange routes with plenty of sight-seeing,
            eating and drinking. Our rides are led by experienced runs leaders</p>
        <p>You don't need to be Chris Boardman to ride with us. We will stop for lunch at a café or a pub where there
            is usually somewhere suitable close by for those who prefer to bring their own packed lunch</p>
        <p>No-one will be left behind, especially not newcomers</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="myCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel" data-interval="3000">
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="2"></li>
        <li data-target="#myCarousel" data-slide-to="3"></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="carousel-inner" role="listbox">
        <div class="carousel-item active">
            <img src="~/images/NewYearsEve2017.jpg" alt="New Years Eve club run" class="d-block w-100" />
            <div class="carousel-caption" role="option">
                <p class="text-primary">
                    New Year's Eve 2017 club run from New Brighton to West Kirby
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img src="~/images/photo1.jpg" alt="Another club run" class="d-block w-100" />
            <div class="carousel-caption" role="option">
                <p>
                    Another club run to somewhere
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img src="~/images/photo2.png" alt="Longer standing members" class="d-block w-100" />
            <div class="carousel-caption" role="option">
                <p>
                    Some of the longer standing members of the club
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img src="~/images/photo3.png" alt="A wet one" class="d-block w-100" />
            <div class="carousel-caption" role="option">
                <p>
                    A wet ride out...
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
    </a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#myCarousel" role="button" data-slide="next">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
    </a>
</div>
